FBIS4-37007 "drnes116_j_94013" FBIS-NES-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen North Said Continuing `Iniquitous' Aggression North Said Continuing `Iniquitous' Aggression EA1506165794 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 15 Jun 94 EA1506165794 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 15 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] A responsible source in the Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY] has issued a statement to the ADEN NEWS AGENCY, in which he reported that the forces of the Sanaa rulers today continued their savage, iniquitous aggression against our people and Republic, the DRY. The source stressed that the aggression against our country and people, and its constant escalation, represented a naked violation of international legitimacy. The source also stressed that the Sanaa rulers were ignoring all appeals calling for an immediate cease-fire put out by worldwide well-wishers, who are anxious to see an end to bloodshed and the restoration of security and stability in Yemen, and in the region.
